commit_list.message: Added git pull help in the read me.
Split view positions are now saved in the document for the main window.
Committing balrog's drag and drop code.
Fixed a crashing but when switching between various streams.
Fixed a lot of warnings after upgrading Xcode.

Merge branch 'master' of github.com:balr0g/Stream

Conflicts:
	Stream/AnalyzerListViewItem.m
The editor list will now update if the sourceUTI changes in the settings popover.
More intelligent about saving window position with file.
Fixing up green "edited" ranges in WFV.
In WFV, in block labels, draw background red if fail.
Added a descriptive string tool tip to explain why blocks fail. Fixed range zooming in WFV.
Closing in on completing the refactoring of cgv.
Fixes crash on window closing. There is still a bug with cached icons in the blocker lists. Some block are displayed as "bad" even if they are "good".
Started moving code out of Color Gradient view and into the cell view controller.
Sorted Blockers Menu. Change CoCo Cassette file block to name block using actual filename. Rearanged Blocker groups.
Removed some NSLogs. Changes image picture pop over to center image.
Fixed Exporting. Not sure why I was releasing that variable.
Bug fixes. I added an “Add stream from URL” function. I fixed MakeSubBlock. Added a pass through option for the raw bit map analyzer. This allows displaying image NSImage already know about.
Ooops. The text view should have been inside a scroll view. All fixed now.

Made the proxy image view clickable. When clicked a popover will display. A list will be available to choose an image. Text files are also supported (with extension 'txt') that allows viewing and editing.
Implemented "suspend observations" to improve blocking speed.
Improved the algorithm on finding LSN0. It can be a tricky basterd.
Change from row background color to indicate "fail" to a "fail icon".
Added expected block size and actual block size methods. Hooked them up to attribute color.

Fixed a load document bug. It caused a crash every time a document was loaded. Added stub resultingData method to BlockerDataAnaylizer for Print Object would start working. In makeMarkForDeleation, I remove all the the sub-sub blocks.
Made re blocking more efficient. And now the Blocks view notices changes after reblocking.
Added a preference to the LSN blocker has a maximum block count. Added a "segment out of range" warning to the OS-9 file blocker.  Made failing color red inherit from parent blocks.
Working on block fail flag. Fixed a stupid CRC transcription bug.
Got the warning icon to display the blocker warning and the analyzer warning, both. Made de-token BASIC and process OS9 Directory files sub classes of the text analyzer.
Added analyzation to remove double bytes from DMK single density disk images. And some other things.
Implemented DMK blocker. Still considering my option for single density "double-byte" mode.
Set up some default text editor views.
Disk BASIC file Block done. Mostly Happy.
Refined the blocker error string view rectangle a little.
Renamed The arbitrary group blocker. Started the basic disk blocker.
Changed Blockers to be a subclass of Blockers. They return string as errors or warnings. There is a new icon in the analyzer bar that lets you view the message.
Invented an arbitrary group blocker. It was the first to get some blocker settings.
I have no idea what I just did.
Re did Core Data model. Over all I think it is an improvement.
Finished the OS-9 file blocker. Works well.
More work on the OS-9 file allocation unit (LSNs) blocker.
Made the IMD blocker not read past the end of the stream.
Added a picture view in the bottom left corner of the list view.
There is no problem a little cache can't solve.
Added DP user interface. Implemented a maximum resync timeout during audio analyzation.
Corrected an error in the "follow pc" disassemble code.
Fixed a bug in the branch handling in the dissasembler.
Fixed some bugs the static analyzer found.
Working on multisegment binary files under the dissasembler.
I kept meaning to add this psd.
Turned on -Wall and -Wextra for my code.
Refining the "Follow PC" mode of the dissasembler.
Started implementing "Follow PC" in the DIssasembly analyzer. Partially working.
Reimplemented audio sample analysis. For the forth time. I really like this one.
Fixed up multiple selections in Block views. Added CoCo segmented object blocker.
Extended the TextAnaylizer to de-tokenize Color Computer Binary BASIC files.
Added photoshop documents for some icons.
Fine tuning UTIs. Fine tuning accessory popover view.
Improved view resizing. Half way implemented "Make Sub Stream".
Fixed buffer overflow crash in zero crossing line drawing. Was that a real commit message?
Switched away from NSTableView to SDListView. Much better.
I need to be better at commit messages.
Wave Form View now shows block ranges.
Working on edit tints in hex view.
More refining of editing in the hex view control.
Starting the process to make the hex editor writable.
Regenerate all blocks after all edits.
Refinement of block and stream uti.
Disabled view controllers if not editable.
Stopped storing frame count and made it a derived value from framebufferobject.
Fixed a whole bunch of stuff.
Implemented more color coding in the blocker view and the wave view.
Added green tints for changed sample in waveformview.
Major refactor to extract the model code from the analyzer view controllers.
Implemented writing in the coco audio analyzer module.
working my way up to writeability.
Started working on support for editing. Fixed a crashing bug on window close.
I think analyzer resizing and collapsing is finally bug free.
Attribute view is working read only.
Half way thru the big view controller rearrangement.
evening commit. I broke a bunch of stuff. Will fix later.
Shortened zoom animation. Got rid of goto.
moved numbers to top in wave form view. This made better use of space with the vanishing scroll bar.
Trying to clean up my changes.
Removed dependency on libsamplerate. I now use Apple's AudioConverter API. GPL license no long required.
started auxiliary view for the action popover. Also added OK and Cancel buttons to to the action popover.
Made options dictions for analyzers KVO and KVC compliant.
Included lib sample rate to allow super zoomed in wave forms to look correct. I guess we're GPL now. :)
Finally fixed the new view layout bug.
worked on audio wave form view.
I finally fixed that stupid xib.
Now with a working editor view election mechanism.
Added better description of CSV files to javascript file.
